Error Message: A subject has a no record in EX but is not populated ARMNRS while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects that have no record in the Exposure domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product should have ARMNRS populated.

Error Message: A subject has a no record in EX but is assigned to a treatment while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects that have no record in the Exposure domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product should not be assigned to a treatment.

Error Message: A subject has a record in EX but is not assigned to a treatment while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects in the Exposure domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product must be assigned to an ARM.

Error Message: Negative value for --PDUR
Description: Value for duration (--PDUR) should not be negative.

Error Message: A subject has a record in EX but is not assigned to a treatment while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects in the Exposure domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product must be assigned to a treatment.

Error Message: Text variables in submitted datasets contain  '.' as an entire value.
Description: Value does not contain any alphanumeric characters other than a period character.

Error Message: '--TPTREF must be populated when --ELTM is populated
Description: '--TPTREF must be populated when --ELTM is populated

Error Message: '--TESTCD does not exist in custom Findings domain.
Description: Raise an error when variable --TESTCD is missing for custom Findings domains

Error Message: Text variables in submitted datasets contain strings which have leading space ' characters
Description: Text variables in submitted datasets should not contain strings which have leading space ' characters

Error Message: '--DTC is greater than --ENDTC
Description: Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--DTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--ENDTC).

Error Message: '--STRESC is numeric but --STRESN is not equal to --STRESC
Description: '--STRESC is populated with a numeric value, but --STRESN is not equal to --STRESC.

Error Message: The End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) is not present in the dataset when Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY) is present.
Description: End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable should be included into dataset, when Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable is present.

Error Message: '--STRESC is populated with a numeric value, but --STRESN is not populated.
Description: When --STRESC is populated with a numeric value, --STRESN should be populated.

Error Message: The Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) is not present in the dataset when Study Day of Start of Observation (--STDY) is present.
Description: Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) variable should be included into dataset, when Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable is present.

Error Message: '--STRESC is not numeric but --STRESN is not empty
Description: '--STRESC is not populated with a numeric value, but --STRESN is not empty.

Error Message: The value is not from the associated codelist, which is not extensible
Description: Raise an error when there is a non-CT value and the associated codelist is not extensible

Error Message: The Collection study day (--DY) is not populated when date/time of collection (--DTC) is populated.
Description: When date/time of collection (--DTC) is populated, the Collection study day (--DY) should also populated.

Error Message: RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' but multiple races are not collected in SUPPDM.
Description: Part A - Raise an error when RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' and SUPPDM dataset is not present.

Error Message: Variables are not in the correct order as shown in SDTM for the observation class.
Description: Raise an error when variables are not in the specified order

Error Message: Subject has no records in EX but ACTARMCD is not equal to SCRNFAIL, NOTASSGN or NOTTRT.
Description: Raise an error when subject has no records in EX but ACTARMCD is not equal to SCRNFAIL, NOTASSGN or NOTTRT.

Error Message: Subject is assigned to an arm code but has no record in EX
Description: If a subject is assigned to an arm code, the subject should have a record in EX.

Error Message: DM dataset is missing.
Description: Raise an error when DM dataset is not present
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-GENETOX, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-AR

Error Message: You have not submitted a dataset named ts.xpt.
Description: A dataset named ts.xpt must be present for each study in Module 4 and in Module 5.

Error Message: Invalid date for TSVAL for TSPARMCD = SSTDTC (Study Start Date)
Description: Raise an error when TSVAL for TSPARMCD=SSTDTC is not a valid date/time

Error Message: No occurrence of TSPARAMCD='CURTRT' is included in TS or TSVAL is null.
Description: At least one occurrence of TSPARAMCD='CURTRT' is included in TS with TSVAL populated.

Error Message: TSVAL does not conform to ISO 8601
Description: When TSPARMCD is equal to AGEMIN and TSVAL is not null, TSVAL should conform to ISO 8601

Description: When TSPARMCD = LENGTH and TSVAL ^= NULL, TSVAL needs to conform to ISO 8601 time period

Error Message: EPOCH values don't match between Subject Visits (SV) and Subject Elements (SE) datasets.
Description: Raise an error when variable EPOCH values don't match between Subject Visits (SV) and Subject Elements (SE) datasets.

Error Message: TSVALCD is not a valid code in the version identified in TSVCDVER.
Description: Raise an error when TSVCDREF ='CDISC' and TSVALCD is not a valid code in the version identified in TSVCDVER.

Error Message: Disposition date time value for DEATH record in DS domain is not the same as DTHDTC value in DM domain
Description: Disposition date time value for DEATH record in DS domain is the same as DTHDTC value in DM domain

Error Message: Date time of collection of subject status in SS domain, where survival status is marked as DEAD, is not on or after the date time of death populated in DM domain.
Description: Date time of collection of subject status in SS domain, where survival status is marked as DEAD, is on or after the date time of death populated in DM domain

Error Message: A subject has a record in DM but not in EX while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects in the Demographics domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product must have at least one corresponding record in the Exposure domain, except for subjects who failed screening, were not fully assigned to an Arm, or did not receive study treatment.

Error Message: A subject has a record in DM but not in EX while participating in an interventional study
Description: All subjects in the Demographics domain who are participating in a study that includes an interventional product must have at least one corresponding record in the Exposure domain, except for subjects who failed screening, were not fully assigned to an Arm, or did not receive study treatment.

Error Message: The set of parameters without conditions listed in the TCG, Appendix B, is not included in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.
Description: The set of parameters without conditions listed in the TCG, Appendix B, is not included in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.

Error Message: No occurrence of TSPARMCD=’CRMDUR’ is included in TS or TSVAL is null.
Description: No occurrence of TSPARMCD=’CRMDUR’ is included in TS or TSVAL is null.

Error Message: TSVAL (Standard Name) does not match corresponding name as listed in on the study data standards resources website for technical specification documents.
Description: TSVAL (Standard Name) matches corresponding name as listed on the study data standards resources website for technical specification documents.

Error Message: There is not a one-to-one relationship between TSVAL and TSVALCD
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between TSVALCD and TSVAL

Error Message: End timing is provided without any starting information

CDISC Rule ID: CG0006, TIG0291, SEND73, TIG0274, SEND74, TIG0275, FB1603
Error Message: '--DY is not calculated correctly even though the date portion of --DTC is complete, the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date, and --DY is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when --DY is not calculated as per the study day algorithm as a non-zero integer value when the date portion of --DTC is complete and the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date AND --DY is not empty
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-GENETOX, SENDIG-AR

Error Message: '--STDTC is greater than --DTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure (--STDTC) must be less or equal to Date/Time of Collection(--DTC)

Error Message: At least one Required variable has a null value
Description: Part B: Raise an error when a Required variable is null.

Error Message: Visit Day cannot be found in Trial Visit (TV) domain
Description: Verify that visitdy is planned and exists in TV

Error Message: SUPP--.RDOMAIN does not represent a dataset present in the study
Description: Trigger error when SUPP--.RDOMAIN does not represent a dataset present in the study

Error Message: DOMAIN Code is not a published DOMAIN Code in CDISC Controlled Terminology.
Description: Raise and error when the DOMAIN Code is not a valid Domain Code published by CDISC.

Error Message: The values of PPCAT and PCTEST do not match at the same reference timepoint
Description: The values of PPCAT and PCTEST do not match at the same reference timepoint

Error Message: AGEU is completed, but both AGE and AGETXT are not completed.
Description: Raise an error when AGEU is completed but both AGETXT and AGE are not completed.

Error Message: Variable label is not in title case.
Description: Raise an error when a variable label is not in title case

Error Message: RFSTDTC must not be null when ACTARM is not in (Screen Failure, Not Assigned, Not Treated.
Description: Raise an error when RFSTDTC is null, but ACTARM is neither Screen Failure, Not Assigned, nor Not Treated

Error Message: RFSTDTC must be null when ACTARM in (Screen failure, Not Assigned, Not Treated).
Description: Raise an error when RFSTDTC is not null, but ACTARM is either Screen Failure, Not Assigned, or Not Treated

Error Message: RFENDTC must not be null when ACTARM is a value other than Screen Failure, Not Assigned, or Not Treated.
Description: Raise an error when RFENDTC is null, but ACTARM is not Screen Failure, Not Assigned, or Not Treated

Error Message: RFENDTC must be null when ACTARM in (Screen Failure, Not Assigned, Not Treated).
Description: Raise an error when RFENDTC is not null, but ACTARM is Screen Failure, Not Assigned, or Not Treated

Error Message: ARM should be equal to ACTARM when ARM is Screen Failure or Not Assigned.
Description: ACTARM value must match ARM value in Demographics when ARM equals "Screen Failure" or "Not Assigned"

Error Message: ARM is not in TA.ARM, but ARM in DM does not equal Screen Failure or Not Assigned.
Description: ARM values in Demographics are restricted to ARM values in Trial Arms when not equal to "Screen Failure" or "Not Assigned"

Error Message: ACTARM should be equal to ARM when ACTARM is Screen Failure or Not Assigned.
Description: Raise an error when ACTARM is Screen Failure or Not Assigned, and ACTARM does not equal ARM

Error Message: ACTARM is not in TA.ARM, but ACTARM in DM does not equal Screen Failure, Not Assigned, Not Treated, or Unplanned Treatment.
Description: Raise an error when no TA.ARM exists for ACTARM in DM and ACTARM does not equal Screen Failure, Not Assigned, Not Treated, or Unplanned Treatment in DM

Error Message: Subject is assigned to an arm but has no record in EX
Description: If a subject is assigned to an arm, the subject should have a record in EX.

Error Message: '--ELTM is not the same value across records with the same values of DOMAIN, VISITNUM, --TPTREF, and --TPTNUM.
Description: Raise an error when --TPT ^= null and --TPTNUM ^= null and --ELTM ^= null and --ELTM does not have the same value across records with the same values of DOMAIN, VISITNUM, --TPTREF, and --TPTNUM.

Error Message: LBSTNRC is populated when LBORRES is a continuous measurement
Description: When LBORRES is a continuous measurement, LBSTNRC should be null

Error Message: Standards units are inconsistent within the same test (category, sub-category, specimen and method)
Description: Standard units should be consistent within the same assessment (having the same --TESTCD, --CAT, --SCAT, --SPEC, --METHOD values)

Error Message: RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' but multiple races are not collected in SUPPDM.
Description: Part C - Raise an error when RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' but no multiple RACE records are present in SUPPDM.

Error Message: RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' but multiple races are not collected in SUPPDM.
Description: Part B -  Raise an error when RACE in DM equals 'MULTIPLE' but no records are present in SUPPDM.

Error Message: No timing variable is provided
Description: There must be at least one timing variable for any of the domains based on the three general observation classes

Error Message: SVUPDES is not populated or does not exist, but the VISIT does not equal a VISIT present in TV
Description: Raise an error when SVUPDES is null and SV.VISIT is not in TV.VISIT

Error Message: SVUPDES is populated, but the VISITNUM equals a VISITNUM present in TV
Description: When SVUPDES is populated, then the VISITNUM should not be equal to a VISITNUM in TV

Error Message: SVUPDES is not populated or does not exist, but the VISITNUM does not equal a VISITNUM present in TV
Description: When SVUPDES is not populated, then the VISITNUM should be equal to a VISITNUM in TV

Error Message: Variable is not an allowed variable for an Observation Class
Description: Trigger error when variable is not an allowed variable for an Observation Class

Error Message: End date time value for an Adverse event with a fatal outcome, is not the same as DTHDTC value in DM domain
Description: End date time value for an Adverse event with a fatal outcome, should be the same as DTHDTC value in DM domain

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when AE.AEOUT is 'FATAL'.
Description: When AE.AEOUT is 'FATAL', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: AEOUT is not "FATAL" and AESDTH is not "Y", when DTHFL="Y"
Description: When the death flag in DM is set to "Y", a record should be present in AE domain, with a fatal outcome and cause of seriousness flagged as death.

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y", when SS.SSSTRESC equals "DEAD"
Description: When survival status is marked as Dead in SS dataset, death flag is populated as Y in DM dataset

Error Message: '--REPNUM is null or is not unique per subject per test per timing variables.
Description: Raise an error when REPNUM is in the dataset and there are multiple records for a subject for a test within the timeframe identified by the timing variables on the record, and --REPNUM is null or not unique per subject per test per timing variables.

Error Message: IDVARVAL does not equal a value of the variable referenced by IDVAR in domain = RDOMAIN.
Description: When IDVAR is populated, IDVARVAL must equal a value of the variable referenced by IDVAR within the domain referenced by RDOMAIN

Error Message: The Collection study day (--DY) is missing when date/time of collection (--DTC) is populated.
Description: When date/time of collection (--DTC) is populated, the Collection study day (--DY) should be present.

Error Message: '--SEQ is not a unique number per USUBJID per domain, nor a unique number per POOLID per domain, including when the domain is split into multiple files
Description: Excluding TS.TSSEQ, raise an error when --SEQ is not a unique number per USUBJID per domain, or not a unique number per POOLID per domain, including when the domain is split into multiple files.

Error Message: TSVAL is not populated with an ISO 21090 null flavor or null flavor description but TSVALNF is populated.
Description: Raise and error when TSVAL is not populated TSVAL is populated with values or synonyms of values in the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist (or other terms that can be represented as null flavors) but TSVALNF is completed.

Error Message: '--CLASCD and --CLAS do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between --CLASCD and --CLAS

Error Message: ACTARMCD and ACTARM do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: ACTARMCD and ACTARM should have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: At least one expected variable is missing from dataset
Description: Raise an error when an expected variable is not present in the dataset.

Error Message: Ethnicity has been collected but the values is not mapped to "HISPANIC OR LATINO" or "NOT HISPANIC OR LATINO"
Description: When Ethnicity was collected and it was not mapped as "HISPANIC OR LATINO" or "NOT HISPANIC OR LATINO".

Error Message: Subject is assigned to an arm but has no record in EX
Description: If a subject is assigned to an arm, the subject should have a record in EX.

Error Message: TSVAL is populated with an ISO 21090 null flavor or null flavor description.
Description: Raise an error when TSVALNF is empty and TSVAL is populated with values or synonyms of values in the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist (or other terms that can be represented as null flavors)

Error Message: ARMCD and ARM do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: ARMCD and ARM should have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: The Study Day of Start of Observation (--STDY) is not present in the dataset when Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) is present.
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable should be included into dataset, when Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) variable is present.

Error Message: '--TESTCD and --TEST do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: '--TESTCD and --TEST should have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: IESCAT exists in a dataset, but IECAT does not exist.
Description: Part B - Raise an error when IESCAT exists in a dataset, but IECAT does not exist.

Error Message: IECAT should not be null when IESCAT is populated
Description: Part B - Raise an error when IESCAT is not empty, but IECAT is empty.

Error Message: TAETORD values don't match between Subject Visits (SV) and Subject Elements (SE) datasets.
Description: Raise an error when variable TAETORD values don't match between Subject Visits (SV) and Subject Elements (SE) datasets.

Error Message: SUPP--.QNAM is present in the dataset, but the value of SUPP--.QNAM equals a variable name defined in the corresponding SDTM version.
Description: Raise an error when SUPP--.QNAM is present in dataset, but value of SUPP--.QNAM is equal to a variable name defined in the corresponding SDTM version.

Error Message: The combination of TESTRL, TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD.
Description: The combination of TESTRL, TEENRL, and TEDUR must be unique for each ETCD.

Error Message: TDSTOFF is not equal to zero or a positive value in ISO 8601 Duration format
Description: TDSTOFF must be equal to 0 or a positive value in ISO 8601 Duration format

Error Message: TP dataset is present.
Description: Raise an error when TP dataset is present.

Error Message: TT dataset is present.
Description: Raise an error when TT dataset is present.

Error Message: '--SCAT exists in a dataset, but --CAT does not exist.
Description: Part A - Raise an error when --SCAT exists in a dataset, but --CAT does not exist.

Error Message: '--CAT should not be null when --SCAT is populated
Description: Part A - Raise an error when --SCAT is not empty, but --CAT is empty.

Description: When an Associated Persons non-supplemental qualifier dataset is associated with a split dataset, the dataset name length must be greater than 4 and less than, or equal to, 6.

Error Message: TM dataset is missing when RELMIDS variable is present in any of the dataset.
Description: Raise an error when variable RELMIDS is present in any of the dataset and TM dataset is missing in a study.

Error Message: collected data fits a Qualifier variable listed in SDTM Sections 2.2.1, 2.2.2, or 2.2.3, and are represented in the Findings About domain, and the name of the variable is used as FATESTCD
Description: Trigger error when collected data fits a Qualifier variable listed in SDTM Sections 2.2.1, 2.2.2, or 2.2.3, and are represented in the Findings About domain, and the name of the variable is used as FATESTCD

Error Message: The Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY) is not present in the dataset when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) is present.
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable should be included into dataset, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable is present.

Error Message: '--STAT = NOT DONE, but a reason is not provided
Description: When a test is not done, the reason why should be populated.

Error Message: Metadata attribute of variable role does not equal the IG role for domain in IG, or model role (for custom domains)
Description: Trigger warning when metadata attribute of variable role does not equal the IG role for domain in IG, or model role (for custom domains)

Error Message: Parent record exists and --DECOD is not null, but FAOBJ is not equal to --DECOD.
Description: When findings are collected, and the parent record exists and --DECOD is not null, FAOBJ should not be equal to --DECOD

Error Message: Related record is present in the parent domain dataset and "Other, specify" value was coded.
Description: When findings are collected, and the Events parent record exists and --DECOD is null, FAOBJ should not be equal to --TERM

Error Message: The submitted dataset is larger than 5 GB
Description: The submitted dataset is larger than 5 GB

Error Message: Timing information is not submitted while it is collected
Description: Time point reference is not provided, when reference time point is used.

Error Message: TSVAL is not a valid preferred term from FDA Substance Registration System (SRS)
Description: TSVAL is a valid preferred term from FDA Substance Registration System (SRS)

Error Message: The length of the variable is longer than the data within the variable
Description: The length of each variable cannot be different between datasets and should not be longer than the maximum length of the data contained by the variable

Error Message: The length of the variable is longer than the data within the variable
Description: All variables in each of the SUPPQUAL and RELREC datasets have a length that is not longer than the length of the longest value for that variable.

Error Message: '--SOCCD is not a valid MedDRA primary system organ class code
Description: Trigger error when --SOCCD is not a valid MedDRA primary system organ class code

Error Message: '--SOC is not a valid MedDRA primary system organ class
Description: Trigger error when --SOC is not a valid MedDRA primary system organ class

Error Message: '--STTPT is equal to the date of collection or assessment but --STRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT',  'UNKNOWN').
Description: Trigger error when --STRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'UNKNOWN')

Error Message: '--BDSYCD is not a valid MedDRA system organ class code
Description: Trigger error when --BDSYCD is not a valid MedDRA system organ class code

Error Message: First 2 characters of prefixed variable within custom domain do not match the DOMAIN value.
Description: Raise an error when the two first characters of a prefixed variable within a custom domain do not match the DOMAIN value.

Error Message: More than 1 record exists per subject per EPOCH with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT' and DSSCAT = 'STUDY TREATMENT'.
Description: Trigger error when subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT' and more than one record where DSSCAT = 'STUDY TREATMENT'

Error Message: More than 1 record exists per subject per EPOCH with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT' and DSSCAT = 'STUDY PARTICIPATION'.
Description: Trigger error when subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT' and more than one record where DSSCAT = 'STUDY PARTICIPATION'

Error Message: TSVCDVER is not a valid published version (date)
Description: Trigger error when TSVCDREF = 'CDISC' and TSVCDVER is not a valid published version (date)

Error Message: LBORRES is not a continuous measurement but LBORNRHI is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when LBORRES is not a continuous measurement and LBORNRHI is not empty. The interpretation of the guidance is that LBORRES is populated (not null).

Error Message: LBORRES is not a continuous measurment but LBSTNRLO is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when LBORRES is not a continuous measurement and LBSTNRLO is not empty. The interpretation of the guidance is that LBORRES is populated (not null).

Error Message: LBORRES is not a continuous measurement but LBSTNRHI is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when LBORRES is not a continuous measurement and LBSTNRHI is not empty. The interpretation of the guidance is that LBORRES is populated (not null).

Error Message: Custom domains use the reserved or modelled standard names.
Description: Raise an error when custom domains use the reserved or modelled standard names

Error Message: AP Core Domain should start with 'AP' and length should be equal to 4.
Description: Raise error if domain name begins with AP and length of domain variable is not 4

Error Message: Variable Core Status = Permissible and data is collected
Description: Variable Core Status = Permissible and data is collected

Error Message: RFCSTDTC is greater than RFCENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin (RFCENDTC).

Error Message: LBORRES is not a continuous measurement but LBORNRLO is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when LBORRES ^= continuous measurement and LBORNRLO is not empty. The interpretation of the guidance is that LBORRES is populated (not null).

Error Message: Variable is empty, where variable core status is expected and data is collected.
Description: Raise an error when variable Core Status = Expected and data is collected, but variable is not present

Error Message: Milestone associated with RFSTDTC is start of treatment and ARMNRS is not null and different from 'UNPLANNED TREATMENT', but RFSTDTC is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when milestone associated with RFSTDTC is start of treatment and ARMNRS is not null and different from 'UNPLANNED TREATMENT', but RFSTDTC is not null.

Error Message: Interventions parent record exists and --DECOD = null, but FAOBJ is not equal to --TRT.
Description: When findings are collected about an intervention, and the interventions parent record exists and --DECOD = null, FAOBJ should be equal to --TRT.

Error Message: An appropriate identifier is not present; USUBJID, APID, SPDEVID, SPTOBID, POOLID, SPTOBID, STOCONID should be present.
Description: APID is required in all Associated Persons Data. In addition to STUDYID, DOMAIN, and --SEQ being required for all domains based on one of the 3 general observation classes, one of USUBJID, APID, SPDEVID, or POOLID must also be present.

Error Message: '--ENDY is not properly calculated per study day algorithm
Description: Study day must be calculated using the algorithm detailed in the SDTMIG.

Error Message: '--STDY is not properly calculated per study day algorithm
Description: Study day must be calculated using the algorithm detailed in the SDTMIG.

Error Message: Verify that LBTOXGR value is not from a numeric scale
Description: Raise a warning when LBTOXGR is not numeric

Error Message: ETCD is not equal to 'UNPLAN' and not equal to TE.ETCD
Description: Raise an error when ETCD is not equal to 'UNPLAN' and not equal to TE.ETCD

Error Message: Haitin or Negro was collected in CRACE but RACE does not have the value as BLACK OR AFRICAN AMERICAN
Description: "Haitian or Negro" was collected and was not mapped as "BLACK OR AFRICAN AMERICAN" in DM domain RACE.

Error Message: Standardized units are not consistent for a given drug or metabolite across pharmacokinetic datasets within a submission.
Description: Standardized units should be consistent for a given drug or metabolite across pharmacokinetic datasets within a submission

Error Message: '--TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship per unique value of VISITNUM
Description: Raise an error when VISITNUM is present in the dataset and --TPTREF is not present in the dataset, and --TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship per unique value of VISITNUM

Error Message: '--TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship per unique value of --TPTREF
Description: Raise an error when VISITNUM is not present in the dataset and --TPTREF is present in the dataset, and --TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship per unique value of --TPTREF

Error Message: '--TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship per unique combination of VISITNUM and --TPTREF values
Description: Raise an error when VISITNUM and --TPTREF are present and --TPT and --TPTNUM does not have a one-to-one relationship per unique combination of VISITNUM and --TPTREF values

Error Message: IDVARVAL and USUBJID are not completed, but IDVAR equals Sequence Number.
Description: Raise an error when IDVARVAL and USUBJID are empty and IDVAR = Sequence Number.

Error Message: Ethnicity(CETHNIC) has been collected as "Spanish origin" but the values in DM is not mapped to "HISPANIC OR LATINO"
Description: When Ethnicity (CETHNIC) "Spanish origin" was collected and was not mapped as "HISPANIC OR LATINO" in DM domain's RACE.

Error Message: OIPARMCD and OIPARM do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between OIPARMCD and OIPARM

Error Message: Related record is present in the parent domain dataset but FAOBJ is not equal to the "TERM", "TRT" or "DECOD" of the parent domain.
Description: Raise an error when a related record is present in the parent domain dataset but FAOBJ is not equal to the --TERM, --TRT or --DECOD of the parent domain.

Error Message: '--SCAT is equal to --BODSYS.
Description: Raise an error when --SCAT = --BODSYS.

Error Message: '--CAT is equal to --BODSYS.
Description: Raise an error when --CAT = --BODSYS.

Error Message: ETCD value is greater than 8
Description: The length of ETCD should be no greater than 8

Error Message: At least one of TEENRL and TEDUR must be populated.
Description: Either TEENRL or TEDUR must be present for each Element.

Error Message: IETESTCD and IETEST do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between IETESTCD and IETEST

Error Message: Dataset LB is missing
Description: Define.xml does not contain ItemGroupDef for the respective Domain with attribute def:HasNoData marked as "Yes"

Error Message: The count of occurrences of TSPARAMCD = PCLASS is in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated is gt 1.
Description: The count of occurrences of TSPARAMCD = PCLASS is in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated is gt 1.

Error Message: Scheduled or Contingent visit is not unique within subject
Description: When VISITNUM is present in TV.VISITNUM, SV.VISITNUM must be unique within subject

Error Message: TSVALNF is not equal to NA when TSPARAMCD=INDIC
Description: TSVALNF is not equal to NA when TSPARAMCD=INDIC

Error Message: STRAIN is present.
Description: Raise an error when STRAIN is present.

Error Message: The set (EGBLIND, EGCTMON, EGLEADPR, EGLEADSM, EGRDMETH, EGREPLBL, EGREPLTR, EGTWVALG) is included in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.
Description: The set (EGBLIND, EGCTMON, EGLEADPR, EGLEADSM, EGRDMETH, EGREPLBL, EGREPLTR, EGTWVALG) is included in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.

Error Message: '--ENRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'ONGOING', 'AFTER', 'UNKNOWN')
Description: Trigger error when --ENRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'ONGOING', 'AFTER', 'UNKNOWN')

Error Message: '--STRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'AFTER', 'UNKNOWN')
Description: Trigger error when --STRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'AFTER', 'UNKNOWN') and --STTPT is prior to the date of collection or assessment.

Error Message: There is not a one-to-one relationship between --BODSYS and --BDSYSCD
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between --BDSYSCD and --BODSYS

Error Message: The set  ('INTMODEL’, 'INTTYPE','PCLASS') is not in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.
Description: The set  ('INTMODEL’, 'INTTYPE','PCLASS') is not in the list of TSPARAMCD with TSVAL populated.

Error Message: A required value of TSPARMCD is not found
Description: A required value of TSPARMCD is not found

Error Message: VISITDY is not null when VISITNUM is not in TV.VISITNUM
Description: Trigger error if VISITDY is populated when VISITNUM is not in TV.

Error Message: EX is not present in study when study includes protocol-specified study treatment
Description: Trigger error when study includes protocol-specified study treatment and EX is not present

Error Message: TSPARAMCD=DCUTDESC and TSPARAMCD=DCUTDTC do not share the same TSGRPID and TSVAL values.
Description: TSPARAMCD=DCUTDESC and TSPARAMCD=DCUTDTC do not share the same TSGRPID and TSVAL values.

Error Message: '--SCAT is equal to --DECOD.
Description: Raise an error when --SCAT = --DECOD.

Error Message: '--CAT is equal to --DECOD.
Description: Raise an error when --CAT = --DECOD.

Error Message: AEREASND is present.
Description: Raise an error when AEREASND is present.

Error Message: Missing --TRTV value, when --VAMT value is populated.
Description: Raise an error when --VAMT is not empty, but --TRTV is empty.

Error Message: '--TOXGR should not be null when --TOX is populated.
Description: Raise an error when --TOX is not empty, but --TOXGR is empty.

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y", when DTHDTC is populated
Description: When a DTHDTC is populated in DM domain, death flag is populated as Y in DM dataset for corresponding subject

Error Message: '--ORRES is missing even though --LOBXFL= "Y" and either --DRVFL is not present in dataset or is not equal to "Y"
Description: Verify that --ORRES is not null when --LOBXFL = Y and --DRVFL= null or --DRVFL is not present in the dataset

Error Message: '--LOBXFL = 'Y', but --STRESC is empty.
Description: Raise an error when --LOBXFL = 'Y' and --STRESC is empty.

Error Message: AGETXT is present.
Description: Raise an error when AGETXT is present.

Error Message: SPECIES is present.
Description: Raise an error when SPECIES is present.

Error Message: SBSTRAIN is present.
Description: Raise an error when SBSTRAIN is present.

Error Message: Value of --LOBXFL must be 'Y' or null
Description: Raise an error when --LOBXFL is not 'Y' or null

Error Message: Missing AESMIE=Y where SUPPAE.QNAM=AESOSP
Description: When SUPPAE.QNAM=AESOSP is present, a record with AESMIE=Y should be present

Error Message: ELEMENT variable has a non-null value when ETCD has a value of 'UNPLAN'
Description: Verify that ELEMENT value is blank when ETCD is equal to UNPLAN

Error Message: AGE and AGETXT are in the list of TSPARAMCDs with TSVAL populated.
Description: Either AGE or AGETXT is in the list of TSPARMCDs with TSVAL populated, not both.

Error Message: DM.RFICDTC is not equal to the earliest DSSTDTC, when DSTERM indicates Informed consent obtained.
Description: DM.RFICDTC must equal the earliest DS.DSSTDTC when DSTERM indicates informed consent obtained.

Error Message: Throw error when TSPARMCD is equal to COMPTRT, CURTRT, or TRT and TSVCDREF ^= UNII
Description: When TSPARMCD is equal to COMPTRT, CURTRT or TRT, TSVCDREF should equal UNII

Error Message: RFENDTC is not blank when ARMNRS is provided.
Description: Raise an error when ARMNRS is not blank and RFENDTC is provided.

Error Message: Value for ARMNRS is populated, when both ARMCD and ACTARMCD values are populated
Description: Verify the value for ARMNRS, when both ARMCD and ACTARMCD values are populated

Error Message: ARMNRS is missing when ARM value is missing
Description: Verify ARMNRS is not null when ARM is null

Error Message: '--BODSYS is not empty and --BDSYCD is empty
Description: Raise an error if --BODSYS is not empty, --BDSYCD is empty

Error Message: ARMNRS value is missing when ARMCD value is missing
Description: Verify ARMNRS is not null when ARMCD is null

Error Message: AEOCCUR is present in AE dataset.
Description: Raise an error when AEOCCUR exists in AE dataset.

Error Message: Supplemental qualifier dataset associated with a split dataset is greater than 8 characters in length
Description: When a supplemental qualifier dataset is associated with a split dataset, the dataset name length must not be greater than 8 characters.

Error Message: ACTARM is empty, but ARMNRS is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when ACTARM is empty and ARMNRS is not completed.

Error Message: ACTARMCD is empty, but ARMNRS is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when ACTARMCD is empty and ARMNRS is not completed.

Error Message: ECDOSE is empty, ECOCCUR is not equal to 'N' and ECSTAT is empty, but ECDOSTXT is also empty.
Description: Raise an error when ECDOSE is empty, ECOCCUR is not equal to 'N', ECSTAT is empty and ECDOSTXT is empty

Error Message: SSSTRESC = 'DEAD', but SSDTC < max DS.DSSTDTC.
Description: Raise an error when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD' and SSDTC < max DS.DSSTDTC.

Error Message: TSPARMCD = RANDQT record is not present
Description: At least one observation where TSPARMCD = TRT is present and there is only one investigational treatment

Error Message: CODTC is populated when IDVAR is also populated
Description: Trigger error when IDVAR is not null and CODTC is not null

Error Message: INVNAM and INVID do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between INVNAM and INVID

Error Message: DSDECOD is not "DEATH", When SS.SSSTRESC = "DEAD".
Description: When SS.SSSTRESC = "DEAD", the final disposition record must have DSDECOD ^= "DEATH".

Error Message: RDOMAIN has a missing value when IDVARVAL has a non-missing value
Description: Verify RDOMAIN is not null when IDVARVAL is not null

Error Message: IDVAR should not be missing when RDOMAIN is not in (empty, DM).
Description: IDVAR must be specified.

Error Message: RDOMAIN has a missing value but IDVAR has a non-missing value
Description: Verify IDVAR is null when RDOMAIN is null

Error Message: Multiple races are collected in SUPPDM but RACE in DM does not equal "MULTIPLE".
Description: Raise an error when multiple races are collected in SUPPDM but RACE in DM does not equal "MULTIPLE".

Error Message: EXVAMT is present when EC exists.
Description: When EC exists, EXVAMT should not be used.

Error Message: One of following variables is not present in the dataset; STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID (or POOLID) or --SEQ.
Description: Raise an error when one of the following variables; STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID (or POOLID) or --SEQ is not present in the dataset.

Error Message: '--ORRES cannot be null when --STAT is null or --DRVFL not equal to 'Y'
Description: Verify that --ORRES is not missing when either --STAT is null or --DRVFL not equal to 'Y'

Error Message: LNKID variable is only found in one domain.
Description: Verify that when --LNKID is present in one domain it is also present in another domain.

Error Message: LNKGRP variable is not found in any of the other domains.
Description: Verify that when --LNKGRP is present in one domain it is also present in another domain.

Error Message: AEPTCD and AEDECOD do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AEPTCD and AEDECOD

Error Message: '--SCAT is equal to --CAT
Description: Trigger error when --SCAT is not null and --SCAT is equal to --CAT

Error Message: '--ENRF is populated when --OCCUR = "N"
Description: When --OCCUR = 'N', --ENRF must not be populated

Error Message: '--TESTCD is equal to 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Raise an error when --TESTCD = 'MULTIPLE'

Error Message: '--ENRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'ONGOING', 'UNKNOWN')
Description: Trigger error when --ENRTPT is not in ('BEFORE', 'COINCIDENT', 'ONGOING', 'UNKNOWN')

Error Message: Length of dataset name of SUPP-- dataset is greater than 8.
Description: Trigger error if length of dataset name is greater than 8

Error Message: '--DIR variable is present, when --LOC variable does not exist in a dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --LOC does not exists in a dataset, --DIR exists.

Error Message: '--PORTOT variable is present, when --LOC variable does not exist in a dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --LOC does not exists in a dataset, --PORTOT exists.

Error Message: Unique RELID is NOT present on multiple RELREC records within a subject.
Description: Within a subject, each unique RELID should be present on multiple RELREC records

Error Message: '--TPTREF is present when --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT are not present.
Description: Raise an error when --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT are not present in dataset, but --TPTREF is present.

Error Message: '--TPTREF must be present when --ELTM is present in a dataset
Description: Raise an error when--ELTM is present but --TPTREF is not present in dataset.

Error Message: '--TPTREF is not present when --RFTDTC is present in a dataset
Description: Raise an error when --TPTREF is not present in dataset when --RFTDTC is present.
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-GENETOX, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-AR

Error Message: '--TOX present in dataset even though --TOXGR is not
Description: Raise an error when --TOXGR is not present in dataset, but --TOX is present

Error Message: AEBDSYCD and AEBODSYS do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AEBDSYCD and AEBODSYS

Error Message: QNAM and QLABEL do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: QNAM and QLABEL should have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: AEHLTCD and AEHLT do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AEHLTCD and AEHLT

Error Message: '--STRF is populated when --OCCUR = "N"
Description: When --OCCUR = 'N', --STRF must not be populated

Error Message: '--REASEX must never be used in SDTM-based human clinical trials
Description: Raise an error when --REASEX is present in dataset.

Error Message: '--EXCLFL must never be used in SDTM-based human trials
Description: Raise an error when --EXCLFL is present in dataset.

Error Message: '--RFTDTC is populated when --TPTREF is null
Description: Trigger error when --TPTREF = null and --RFTDTC is populated
Standard Name: SDTMIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-GENETOX, TIG, SENDIG-AR

Error Message: '--TPTREF is empty and --ELTM is not empty
Description: Raise an error when --TPTREF is empty, but --ELTM is not empty

Error Message: '--ENRTPT is completed, but --ENTPT is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when --ENRTPT is completed and --ENTPT is not completed.
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-AR, SENDIG-GENETOX

Error Message: RFICDTC is greater than RFXSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC)

Error Message: RFXSTDTC is greater than RFXENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: '--DTC is greater than RFPENDTC
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: AEHLGTCD and AEHLGT do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AEHLGTCD and AEHLGT

Error Message: '--STDTC is greater than --ENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDTC).

Error Message: AESTDTC is greater than max(DSSTDTC)
Description: Start Date/Time of Adverse Event (AESTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: AESOCCD and AESOC do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AESOCCD and AESOC

Error Message: VISITDY is populated when SVPRESP is null.  VISITDY is the Planned Study Day of a visit. It should not be populated for unplanned visits.
Description: Raise an error when SVPRESP is null and VISITDY is not null.

Error Message: Planned visit is not found in TV.
Description: Raise an error when SVPRESP is "Y" and VISIT is not present in TV.VISIT.

Error Message: VISITNUM for unplanned visit is present in TV.
Description: Raise an error when SVPRESP is null and VISITNUM is present in TV.VISITNUM

Error Message: VISITNUM for planned visit is not in TV.
Description: Raise an error when SVPRESP="Y" and VISITNUM is not in TV.VISITNUM

Error Message: Parent domain referenced in Findings About dataset name is not present in the study
Description: Raise an error when parent domain referenced in Findings About dataset name is not present in the study.

Error Message: SVPRESP is not "Y" when SVOCCUR is populated.
Description: Raise an error when SVOCCUR is not null and SVPRESP is not "Y".

Error Message: SVPRESP is not null and not equal to "Y". Values should be "Y" or null.
Description: Raise an error when SVPRESP not "Y" or null.

Error Message: For the same analyte, specimen type are not consistent across pharmacokinetic datasets within a submission.
Description: For the same analyte, specimen type should be consistent across pharmacokinetic datasets within a submission.

Error Message: RFICDTC is greater than RFSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: '--STDTC is greater than RFPENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time (--STDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: ARM value in DM dataset is not among the values of ARM variable in TA dataset. This is allowed only in a multistage study with incomplete ARM assignment. Please confirm if your study is a multistage assignment study
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARM is populated, ARM must be present in TA.ARM. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARM is not present in TA.ARM and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: ACTARMCD is not in TA.ARMCD
Description: Trigger error when study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ACTARMCD ^= null, and ACTARMCD is not in TA.ARMCD

Error Message: ACTARM value in DM dataset is not among the values of ARM variable in the TA dataset. This is allowed only in a multistage study with incomplete ARM assignment. Please confirm if your study is a multistage assignment study.
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ACTARM is populated, ACTARM must be present in TA.ARM. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ACTARM is not present in TA.ARM and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: AGE is missing when AGEU is provided.
Description: Raise an error when AGEU is not blank and AGE is blank.

Error Message: AGEU is missing when AGE is provided.
Description: Raise an error when AGE is not blank and AGEU is blank.

Error Message: '--METHOD is present in an interventions domain.
Description: Raise an error when --METHOD is present in an Interventions dataset.

Error Message: There are no DS records for subject who was assigned treatment
Description: When ACTARMCD is populated, disposition data for subject must be present

Error Message: There is more than one record per subject per EPOCH
Description: Trigger error when there is more than one record per subject per EPOCH

Error Message: More than one record per subject per DSSCAT per EPOCH
Description: Trigger error when there is more than one record per subject per DSSCAT per EPOCH

Error Message: DSSCAT is not present when subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT'.
Description: When subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT, DSSCAT must be present.

Error Message: AECONTRT is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AECONTRT is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESDISAB is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESDISAB is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESMIE is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESMIE is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESOD is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESOD is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESLIFE is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESLIFE is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESHOSP is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESHOSP is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESDTH is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESDTH is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESCONG is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESCONG is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESCAN is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESCAN is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: AESER is completed, but not equal to "N" or "Y"
Description: Raise an error when AESER is completed and value is not 'Y' or 'N'

Error Message: IDVAR does not represent a variable present in the dataset identified in RDOMAIN
Description: When IDVAR is populated, IDVAR must be a valid variable in the domain referenced by RDOMAIN.

Error Message: RFENDTC is missing when ARM is provided.
Description: Raise an error when ARM is not empty and RFENDTC is empty.

Error Message: ARM is populated, when ARMCD is NULL
Description: Raise an error when ARM is not empty, but ARMCD is empty

Error Message: ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: ACTARM is populated, when ACTARMCD is NULL
Description: Raise an error when ACTARM is not empty, but ACTARMCD is empty

Error Message: TSVAL is not in ISO 8601 format
Description: Trigger error when TSPARMCD = 'AGEMAX' and TSVAL ^= null and TSVAL does not conform to ISO 8601

Error Message: AESTAT variable is present in AE dataset.
Description: Raise an error when AESTAT is present in AE dataset.

Error Message: DVSTDTC is earlier than RFICDTC in DM.
Description: Raise an error when DVSTDTC is earlier than RFICDTC in DM.

Error Message: DSSTDTC does not equal DM.DTHDTC, when DSDECOD equals "DEATH".
Description: Raise an error when DSSTDTC is not equal to DM.DTHDTC and DSDECOD is equal to "DEATH"

Error Message: The earliest disposition date for "INFORMED CONSENT OBTAINED" is not equal to DM.RFICDTC
Description: When there are multiple informed consents obtained and DSDECOD = 'INFORMED CONSENT OBTAINED', the earliest DSSTDTC for each subject should be equal to DM.RFICDTC.

Error Message: '--ENTPT is completed, but --ENRTPT is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when --ENTPT is completed and --ENRTPT is not completed.

Error Message: '--DECOD should be populated when --PTCD is populated
Description: Raise an error when --DECOD is not populated but --PTCD is populated

Error Message: '--DECOD and --PTCD do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: Trigger error when --DECOD and --PTCD do not have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: '--STRESU is null when --STRESC ^= null and units are applicable for the result
Description: Trigger error if --STRESU is null when --STRESC ^= null and units are applicable for the result

Error Message: TATRANS is null when trial Design allows for a Subject to transition to an Element other than the next Element in sequence
Description: Trigger error when trial Design allows for a Subject to transition to an Element other than the next Element in sequence, and TATRANS is null

Error Message: TIVERS is null when there is more than one version of the IE criteria in study documentation
Description: Trigger error when TIVERS is null and there is more than one version of the IE criteria in study documentation

Error Message: SREL does not describe the relationship of associated person to study identified in STUDYID when RSUBJID = null and RDEVID = null
Description: Trigger error when RSUBJID = null and RDEVID = null and SREL does not describe the relationship of associated person to study identified in STUDYID

Error Message: TSVCDVER is null when Reference Terminology is versioned
Description: Trigger error when Reference Terminology is versioned and TSVCDVER is null

Error Message: RFSTDTC is greater than RFENDTC
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) must be less than or equal to Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Error Message: Variable type in dataset does not variable datatype in the define.xml
Description: Trigger error when variable type does not match IG Type (for domains in IG) or Model Type (custom domains)

Error Message: PP dataset is present in  study, but PC dataset is not present in study.
Description: Raise an error when a PP dataset is present in study, but a PC dataset is not present in study.

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when DS.DSDECOD is "DEATH"
Description: When DS.DSDECOD is 'DEATH', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when AE.AESDTH is 'Y'.
Description: When AE.AESDTH is 'Y', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: DD record present for subject, but DTHFL is not equal to "Y".
Description: When a record is present in DD domain for a subject, death flag is populated as Y in DM dataset for corresponding subject

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y" or null
Description: Raise an error when DTHFL ^= "Y" and not null

Error Message: '--ENTPT should be present when --ENRTPT is present in a dataset
Description: Raises an error when --ENRTPT is present in dataset but --ENTPT is not present in dataset.

Error Message: '--ENTPT exists in a dataset, but --ENRTPT does not exist.
Description: Raise an error when --ENTPT exists in a dataset and --ENRTPT does not exist.

Error Message: '--STRTPT is present in dataset, but --STTPT is not present in dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --STRTPT is present in dataset and --STTPT is not present in dataset.

Error Message: '--STRTPT is completed, but --STTPT is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when --STRTPT is completed and --STTPT is not completed.
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-AR, SENDIG-GENETOX

Error Message: '--STTPT is completed and --STRTPT is empty
Description: Raise an error when --STTPT is completed and --STRTPT is empty

Error Message: '--STTPT is present in dataset, but --STRTPT is not present in dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --STTPT is present in dataset and --STRTPT is not present in dataset.

Error Message: TSPARM and TSPARMCD don't have a one-to-one relationship.
Description: Raise an error when TSPARM and TSPARMCD don't have a one-to-one relationship.
Standard Name: SDTMIG, TIG, SENDIG, SENDIG-GENETOX, SENDIG-DART, SENDIG-AR

Error Message: Length of ARMCD is greater than 20
Description: The length of ARMCD is limited to 20 characters.

Error Message: TSVAL is null when TSVAL1 is populated.
Description: Trigger error when TSVAL1 is populated and TSVAL is null

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when CETERM or CEDECOD  = 'DEATH'.
Description: When CETERM or CEDECOD  = 'DEATH', DTHFL MUST BE 'Y'.

Error Message: '--STDY is greater than --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Start of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDY).

Error Message: '--DY is greater than --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Observation (--DY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY)

Error Message: AELLTCD and AELLT do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between AELLTCD and AELLT

Error Message: The death flag in DM is set to "Y", but death date is not populated on corresponding record
Description: When the death flag in DM is set to "Y", then death date is populated on corresponding record

Error Message: '--STDY is not null when either --STDTC or DM.RFSTDTC do not contain complete values in their date portion
Description: If --STDTC or DM.RFSTDTC does not contain a complete values, --STDY must be null.

Error Message: SEENDTC is null when element is not the last.
Description: Trigger error where element is not the last element and SEENDTC is null.

Error Message: IEORRES is not equal to 'Y' when IECAT equals 'EXCLUSION'.
Description: Raise an error when IECAT is equal to 'EXCLUSION' and IEORRES is not equal to 'Y'.

Error Message: IEORRES is not equal to 'N' when IECAT equals 'INCLUSION'.
Description: Raise an error when IECAT is equal to 'INCLUSION' and IEORRES is not equal to 'N'.

Error Message: '--TPT and --TPTNUM do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: Trigger error when VISITNUM and --TPTREF are not present and --TPT and --TPTNUM does not have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: RELREC.RDOMAIN does not represent a dataset present in the study
Description: RELREC.RDOMAIN must represent a dataset that is present in the study.

Error Message: EPOCH is missing for clinical subject-level observations
Description: EPOCH should be included for clinical subject-level observations

Error Message: The Date/Time of Collection (--DTC)  is not present in the dataset when Study Day of Visit/Collection/Exam (--DY) is present.
Description: Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) variable should be included into dataset, when Collection Study Day (--DY) variable is present.

Error Message: ARM is not in TA.ARM
Description: Trigger error when ARM is populated and ARM is not in TA.ARM

Error Message: ARMCD is not in TA.ARMCD
Description: Trigger error when ARMCD is populated and ARMCD is not in TA.ARMCD

Error Message: There is not a one-to-one relationship between TSVAL and TSVALCD
Description: When TSVAL and TSVALCD are populated, there must be a one-to-one relationship between TSVALCD and TSVAL

Error Message: '--TERM is equal to 'OTHER'
Description: Raise an error when --TERM = 'OTHER'

Error Message: Length of TSPARM is greater than 40
Description: Trigger error when length of TSPARM value is greater than 40

Error Message: '--TERM is equal to 'MULTIPLE'

Description: Value for Parameter Null Flavor (--VALNF) variable should be NULL, when Parameter Value (--VAL) variable value can be populated.

Error Message: Missing values for both --VAL and --VALNF
Description: Value for Parameter Value (--VAL) variable must be populated. --VAL can only be null when Parameter Null Flavor (--VALNF) variable value is populated.

Error Message: Value for --SOCCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for System Organ Class Code (--SOCCD) variable must be populated using a System Organ Class Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --SOC is in incorrect case
Description: Case for System Organ Class (--SOC) variable must be sentence case using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --SOC not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for System Organ Class (--SOC) variable must be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --BDSYCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) variable should be populated using a System Organ Class Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --HLGTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Group Term Code (--HLGTCD) variable must be populated using a High Level Group Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --HLGT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for High Level Group Term (--HLGT) variable must be sentence case using a High Level Group Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --HLGT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Group Term (--HLGT) variable must be populated using a High Level Group Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --HLTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Term Code (--HLTCD) variable must be populated using a High Level Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --HLT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for High Level Term (--HLT) variable must be sentence case using a High Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --HLT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Term (--HLT) variable must be populated using a High Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --LLTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Lowest Level Term Code (--LLTCD) variable must be populated using a Lowest Level Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --LLT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for Lowest Level Term (--LLT) variable must be sentence case using a Lowest Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --LLT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Lowest Level Term (--LLT) variable must be populated using a Lowest Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Unexpected MedDRA coding in the SUPPQUAL domain
Description: MedDRA coding info should be populated using variables in the Events General Observation Class, but not in SUPPQUAL domains.

Error Message: Value for --PTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Missing value for DTHDTC, when DTHFL is populated
Description: Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) should be provided, when subject died (DTHFL=Y).

Error Message: Missing value for DTHFL, when DTHDTC is populated
Description: Subject Death Flag (DTHFL) value must equal 'Y', when Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) is provided.

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARM
Description: Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('Screen Failure'), or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('Not Assigned'), or randomized, but not treated ('Not Treated') or received non-planned treatment ('Unplanned Treatment').

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARMCD
Description: Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('SCRNFAIL'),  or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('NOTASSGN'),  or randomized but not treated ('NOTTRT'), or received non-planned treatment ('UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARMCD
Description: The value of Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (DISEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID)

Error Message: Missing --STINT variable, when --ENINT variable is present
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable must be included in the domain, when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --ENINT variable, when --STINT variable is present
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable must be included in the domain, when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing values for one or more variables subject to MedDRA: --LLT, --LLTCD, --DECOD, --PTCD, --HLT, --HLTCD, --HLGT, --HLGTCD, --BODSYS, --BDSYCD, --SOC, --SOCCD
Description: Reported Term for the Adverse Event (AETERM) is expected to be coded using the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Affairs (MedDRA). Sponsors should code each term to the MedDRA-specified hierarchy of terms. These terms/codes are represented in SDTM variables that are subject to MedDRA: AELLT, AELLTCD, AEDECOD, AEPTCD, AEHLT, AEHLTCD, AEHLGT, AEHLGTCD, AEBODSYS, AEBDSYCD, AESOC, AESOCCD.

Error Message: '--STRESN is populated when --STRESC value is not numeric
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be null when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value does not represent a numeric value, (e.g. 'BLQ', value contains '<' or '>', etc.).

Error Message: Exposure start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: Multiple --LOBXFL records for the same test
Description: By its definition Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with  Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Position of Subject During Observation (--POS), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC) and Laterality (--LAT).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --SOC within --TERM
Description: MedDRA System Organ Class (--SOC) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BODSYS within --TERM
Description: Body System (--BODSYS) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --HLGT within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding High Level Group Term (--HLGT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --HLT within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding High Level Term (--HLT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --DECOD within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding Preferred Term (--DECOD) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Multiple BASELINE records for the same test
Description: By its definition clinical baseline flags (e.g., last non-missing value prior to first dose) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with Baseline Flag (--BLFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT) and Directionality (--DIR).

Error Message: No subject identifier variables are populated
Description: At least one of the following subject identifier variables must be populated for each record: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Associated Persons Identifier (APID), Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID), or Pool Identifier (POOLID).

Error Message: ETCD value not present in SE
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Subject Elements (SE).

Error Message: ETCD value not present in TA
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned for at least one Arm Code (ARMCD) in Trial Arms (Trial Arms).

Error Message: No records for SCREEN FAILURE subject are found in IE domain
Description: All subjects with Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) equal to 'SCREEN FAILURE' should have records in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) domain.

Error Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a treated subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all treated subjects, those where Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTASSGN' or 'NOTTRT' (or null).

Error Message: RFENDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFENDTC must be null when actual arm indicates that the subject is a screen failure ('Screen Failure'), was not assigned to an arm ('Not Assigned'), or was not treated ('NOTTRT') (or null). This rule applies to studies where RFENDTC is associated with a treatment date.

Error Message: No Disposition record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) should have at least one record in the Disposition (DS) domain with only possible exceptions to subjects who did not receive treatment (ACTARMCD is null).

Error Message: RFSTDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFSTDTC must be null when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated (excluding values of UNPLANNED TREATMENT), which indicates that the subject did not receive treatment.

Error Message: '--STRESC is null when --LOBXFL = 'Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y'.

Error Message: '--ORRES is null when --LOBXFL = 'Y' (and --DRVFL is null)
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y', unless the record is derived (--DRVFL = 'Y').

Error Message: '--STREFN is null when --STREFC is populated
Description: Numeric Reference Result in Std Units (--STREFN) should be populated when Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) is populated.

Error Message: '--STREFC is null when --ORREF is populated
Description: Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) should be populated when Reference Result in Original Units (--ORREF) is populated.

Error Message: SMSTDTC is null
Description: Start Date/Time of Milestone (SMSTDTC) should not be null. The start date/time of the Disease Milestone is the critical date/time, and must be populated.

Error Message: Multiple disposition events for the same DSSCAT and EPOCH
Description: There should be at most one disposition event record per subject per Subcategory for Disposition Event (DSSCAT) per Epoch. If multiple disposition events are reported for a Subcategory for DSSCAT and EPOCH, the sponsor should identify a primary reason and use that to populate DSTERM and DSDECOD. Additional reasons should be submitted in SUPPDS.

Error Message: RFENDTC is populated when ARMNRS is not null
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be null for screen failures or unassigned subjects. Therefore, when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated, RFENDTC should be null.

Error Message: ADSL Population Flags provided in SDTM
Description: ADSL Population Flags, which had standard Supplemental Qualifiers included in previous versions of the SDTMIG (COMPLT, FASFL/FULLSET, ITT, PPROTFL/PPROT, SAFFL/SAFETY, etc.) should no longer be used in SDTM.

Error Message: ACTARMCD/ACTARM is populated for a subject who wasn't treated
Description: Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) and Actual Arm (ACTARM) must be null for subjects who weren't treated. This includes Screen Failure subjects, Not Assigned subjects, and Not Treated subjects.

Error Message: ARMCD/ARM is populated for a subject not assigned to treatment
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must not be null for subjects who are not assigned to treatment. This includes Screen Failure subjects and Not Assigned subjects.

Error Message: ACTARM is populated, but ACTARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) must be populated, when Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Error Message: ARM is populated, but ARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must be populated, when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Error Message: ARMNRS is populated but ARMCD and ACTARMCD are populated
Description: The Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable should only be populated when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) are null.

Error Message: ARMNRS is not populated when ARMCD/ARM are not provided
Description: When Planned Arm Code (ARMCD)/Description of Planned Arm (ARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ARMCD/ARM are null.

Error Message: ARMNRS is not populated, when ACTARMCD or ACTARM is NULL
Description: When Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD)/Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ACTARMCD/ACTARM are null.

Error Message: MIDSDTC variable is present when MIDS variable is missing
Description: Disease Milestone Instance Date/Time (MIDSDTC) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is missing.

Error Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable RELMIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Temporal Relation to Milestone Instance (RELMIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Error Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable MIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Error Message: ARMCD value not present in DM
Description: Arm Code (ARMCD) values defined in Trial Arms (TA) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Demographics (DM).

Error Message: '--STRESC does not equal --ORRES when --STRESU is equal to --ORRESU
Description: Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value should be equal to Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) variable value, when variable values are numeric and Standard Units (--STRESU) and Original Units (--ORRESU) are populated with the same units or are null.

Error Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Interventions class domains should be one record per Intervention Episode per subject. No Interventions with the same Treatment (--TRT), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Mood (--MOOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Route (--ROUTE), Location (--LOC) and Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) with the same Start Date (--STDTC), Planned Time Point Name (--TPT), and Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) are expected.

Error Message: Missing value for --STINT, when --ENINT is provided
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) should not be NULL, when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --ENINT, when --STINT is provided
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) should not be NULL, when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) is populated.

Error Message: Inconsistent STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values should be consistent for all subjects in the Demographics (DM) domain for one study.

Error Message: Missing values for --STINT and --ENINT variables when --TEST references 'T1 to T2'
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) and Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variables should be present and populated when Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) is over a time interval, 'T1 to T2', where 'T1' is represented by the value in --STINT and 'T2' is represented by the value in --ENINT.

Error Message: AEENDTC for fatal AE is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: Fatal Adverse Event records (AEOUT = 'FATAL') in the Adverse Events (AE) domain should have End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Error Message: Value for --CLASCD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class Code (--CLASCD) variable must be populated using ATC Code from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --CLAS not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class (--CLAS) variable must be populated using ATC Text from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when subject is treated
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when subject is treated (ACTARMCD is not 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTTRT', 'NOTASSGN', or null).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Standardized Medication Name (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Drug Name from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when RFXENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC)variable value is provided.

Error Message: EX record is present, when subject is not treated
Description: Subjects that are not treated (ACTARMCD='NOTTRT' or null) should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Error Message: Missing EPOCH value, when a start or observation date is provided
Description: The EPOCH variable is not populated, however either a start date or a collection date is provided. The presence of a start date or collection date for a record should allow for the EPOCH variable to be populated. Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents (e.g., EPOCH) should be included in the dataset and populated.

Error Message: RSLNKGRP value does not exist in TR domain
