Description: A Link Group (RSLNKGRP) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Error Message: RSLNKID value does not exist in TR domain
Description: A Link ID (RSLNKID) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Error Message: TRLNKID value does not exist in TU domain
Description: A Link ID (TRLNKID) value for a tumor that is referenced in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Identification (TU) domain for that subject.

Error Message: RFICDTC is after RFXSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).

Error Message: RFICDTC is after RFSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: AEOUT = RECOVERED/RESOLVED, but an end date or collected duration is not provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value RECOVERED/RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) or Duration of Adverse Event (AEDUR) variables are null. If the adverse event has an outcome of RECOVERED/RESOLVED, it is expected that an end date or a collected duration be provided.

Error Message: AEOUT = NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, but an end date is provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) variable is populated with an end date for the adverse event. If the adverse event has an outcome of NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, it is expected that no end date is available.

Error Message: '--STDTC is after --DTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure (--STDTC) must be less or equal to Date/Time of Collection(--DTC)

Error Message: '--DY is after --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Observation (--DY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY)

Error Message: RSUBJID is equal to USUBJID
Description: The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to USUBJID.

Error Message: RSUBJID is equal to POOLID
Description: The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to Pool Identifier (POOLID).

Error Message: RDEVID is not null when RSUBJID is populated
Description: Related Device Identifier (RDEVID) and Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) should not both be populated for the same record.

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset description mismatch
Description: Dataset Description in define.xml must match dataset Description.

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in define.xml must match variable Label in dataset.

Error Message: Value for COUNTRY not found in ISO 3166
Description: Value for the Country (COUNTRY) variable must be populated using terms found in ISO 3166.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for FCNTRY
Description: TSVAL for FCNTRY record must be a valid term from ISO 3166.

Error Message: No Treatment Emergent info for Adverse Event (missing SUPPAE)
Description: A treatment-emergent flag should be included in SUPPAE according to the FDA business rule that states, 'A treatment-emergent flag should be submitted.'

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STAT is null
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Completion Status (--STAT) value is NULL.

Error Message: '--STDTC is before RFICDTC
Description: All records in the Disposition (DS) and Protocol Deviations (DV) domains should have the Start Date/Time of Event (--STDTC) equal to or after a subject's Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) in the Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: No records for subject are found in DV domain
Description: Subjects who have DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL VIOLATION' or DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL DEVIATION' records in the Disposition (DS) domain should have supportive records with details in the Protocol Deviations (DV) domain.

Error Message: DSSTDTC for DEATH record is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: DEATH records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in the Disposition (DS) domain should have Start Date of Event (DSSTDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Error Message: Missing 'DEATH' record for subject in DS domain
Description: All subjects who have Death records (SSSTRESC = 'DEAD') in Survival Status (SS) domain should also have death records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in Disposition (DS) domain.

Error Message: DSDECOD is not the same as DSTERM, when DSCAT='PROTOCOL MILESTONE'
Description: Reported Term for the Disposition Event (DSTERM) and Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) should contain the same value, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) is 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'.

Error Message: DSDECOD is not 'COMPLETED', when DSTERM='COMPLETED'
Description: When Reported Term for the Disposition Event (DSTERM) is 'COMPLETED', Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) should have the same value 'COMPLETED'.

Error Message: Missing EPOCH value, when DSCAT is 'DISPOSITION EVENT'
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) variable should be provided, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) equals 'DISPOSITION EVENT'.

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the PCLAS Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Pharmacologic Class parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'PCLAS').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTTYPE Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Type parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTTYPE').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTMODEL Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Model parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTMODEL').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the TRT Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Investigational Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TRT').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the CURTRT Trial Summary Parameter, when ADDON parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When test product is added to existing treatment (TSPARMCD = 'ADDON' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Current Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'CURTRT').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'N'
Description: When the study population is not healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'N'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Error Message: The TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter is not provided with TSVAL equal to null, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When the study population is healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with a null Parameter Value (TSVAL should be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Error Message: Invalid value for TDSTOFF variable
Description: Offset from the Anchor (TDSTOFF) variable value must be either 0, ISO 8601 format for duration (e.g. P80Y), or null.

Error Message: Invalid value for DOMAIN variable
Description: The value of DOMAIN should be no more than 2 characters in length, excluding Associated Persons domains.

Error Message: No timing variables are present in dataset
Description: All domains based on the general observation classes (Interventions, Events, Findings) should have at least one Timing variable present.

Error Message: LBTOXGR is not a numeric value when a numeric scale is used.
Description: When a numeric scale is used (Grade 1, Grade 2, etc.), LBTOXGR should only contain the number.

Error Message: TSVAL is populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist
Description: TSVAL should not be populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist, or synonyms of the values. The TSVALNF variable should be used to capture these values, not TSVAL.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADAPT parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADAPT record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADDON parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADDON record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: '--STAT variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Error Message: '--REASND variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRTPT, when --STTPT is populated
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) must be populated when Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --ENRTPT, when --ENTPT is populated
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) must be populated when End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) is populated.

Error Message: Multiple disposition events for the same EPOCH
Description: If multiple disposition events are reported for an EPOCH, the sponsor should identify a primary reason and use that to populate DSTERM and DSDECOD. Additional reasons should be submitted in SUPPDS.

Error Message: Missing value for --DECOD, when --PTCD is populated
Description: Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be populated when Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) is populated.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --PTCD within --DECOD
Description: All values of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) should be the same for a given value of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --DECOD within --PTCD
Description: All values of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be the same for a given value of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD).

Error Message: IETESTCD is not unique within TIVERS
Description: A value of Incl/Excl Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be unique within a version of inclusion/exclusion criteria (TIVERS).

Error Message: '--DIR variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Directionality (--DIR) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: '--PORTOT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Portion or Totality (--PORTOT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: '--LAT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Laterality (--LAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: '--TPTREF variable is present when --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT are missing
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable, Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, and Planned Time Point (--TPT) variable are missing.

Error Message: '--TOX variable is present when --TOXGR variable is missing
Description: Toxicity (--TOX) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable is missing.

Error Message: ECDOSTXT is null when ECDOSE is null and ECOCCUR does not equal 'N'
Description: Dose Description (ECDOSTXT) should be populated when Dose (ECDOSE) is null, ECOCCUR does not equal 'N', and ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE'.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for TSVALCD within TSVAL
Description: Parameter Value Code (TSVALCD) and Parameter Value (TSVAL) should have a one-to-one relationship.

Error Message: '--TERM equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: '--TRT equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: '--TESTCD equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: '--TERM equals 'OTHER'
Description: Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: '--TRT equals 'OTHER'
Description: Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: '--TESTCD equals 'OTHER'
Description: Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD
Description: The combination of Description of Element (ELEMENT), Rule for Start of Element (TESTRL), Rule for End of Element (TEENRL), and Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be unique for each Element Code (ETCD).

Error Message: Missing PC dataset, when PP dataset is present
Description: Pharmacokinetic Concentrations (PC) dataset should be included, when a Pharmacokinetic Parameters(PP) dataset is present.

Error Message: TSVAL is not between 0 and 1, when TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'
Description: For the trial summary parameter Randomization Quotient (TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'), the value must always be a number between 0 and 1, with some cases where the ratio might be equal to 1.

Error Message: TSVCDREF is null when TSVCDVER is populated
Description: The Name of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDREF) must be populated when the Version of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDVER) is populated.

Error Message: Invalid value for TAETORD
Description: Planned Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) variable value must be an integer.

Error Message: ETCD equals 'UNPLAN' when SEUPDES is null
Description: When the Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) is not populated, the Element Code (ETCD) should not be equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: QEVAL is null when QORIG equals 'ASSIGNED'
Description: For subjective data (when QORIG='ASSIGNED'), QEVAL should be populated and the value should reflect the role of the person or institution assigning the value.

Error Message: IDVAR equals --SEQ when IDVARVAL is null and USUBJID is null
Description: When the RELREC dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets (in which case USUBJID and IDVARVAL are left null), instead of relating individual records, --SEQ cannot be used for IDVAR because --SEQ only has meaning within a subject within a dataset, not across datasets.

Error Message: MBRESCAT is null when MBTESTCD = 'ORGANISM'
Description: MBRESCAT is expected to be populated in all records where a microorganism has been identified (MBTESTCD = 'ORGANISM'), excluding records where MBSTRESC equals 'NO GROWTH' or MBMETHOD equals 'GRAM STAIN'.

Error Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DSSTDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Start Date/Time of Disposition Event (DSSTDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

Error Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DTHDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

Error Message: TSVCDVER is null when Reference Terminology is versioned
Description: The Version of the Reference Terminology variable (TSVCDVER) should be populated with the version number of the Reference Terminology, when that Reference Terminology is versioned.

Error Message: Invalid value for SETCD
Description: The value of Set Code (SETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFSTDTC must be null when actual arm indicates that the subject is a screen failure ('Screen Failure'), was not assigned to an arm ('Not Assigned'), was not treated ('NOTTRT'), or actual arm is null. This rule applies to studies where RFSTDTC is associated with a treatment date.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DS.DSDECOD = 'DEATH'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Disposition (DS) domain with DSDECOD = 'DEATH'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AESDTH = 'Y'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AESDTH = 'Y'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AEOUT = 'FATAL'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AEOUT = 'FATAL'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DD record is present
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Death Details (DD) domain.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when SS.SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Subject Status (SS) domain with SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'.

Error Message: '--VAMTU is not null when --TRTV is null
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) value must be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--TRTV) value is null.

Error Message: Missing --TPTNUM variable, when --TPT variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable is present.

Error Message: EXDOSE does not equal 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'
Description: EXDOSE must be equal to 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'.

Error Message: ECDOSE is not null or greater than 0 when ECOCCUR = 'N'
Description: ECDOSE must either be null when ECOCCUR equals 'N', or ECDOSE must be greater than 0. ECDOSE would be greater than 0 (when ECOCCUR equals N) for records that represent specific dose amounts that are not taken, not given, or missed.

Error Message: ECDOSE is not greater than 0 when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' and ECDOSTXT is null
Description: ECDOSE must be greater than zero when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' , ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', and ECDOSTXT is null. ECDOSE must not be set to zero (0) as an alternative method for indicating doses not taken, not given, or missed.

Error Message: Missing --TPTREF variable, when --ELTM variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --TPT variable, when --TPTNUM variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable is present.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BDSYCD within --BODSYS
Description: All values of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BODSYS within --BDSYCD
Description: All values of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD).

Error Message: '--BODSYS is not populated when --BDSYCD is populated
Description: Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) must be populated when Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) is populated.

Error Message: No Informed Consent Obtained record in DS domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have an Informed Consent record in the Disposition domain.

Error Message: Duplicate records in Device Property
Description: There should be one record per device property defined by SPDEVID and DOTESTCD variables

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each combination of Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) and Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables' values.

Error Message: Neither SPDEVID nor USUBJID values are populated
Description: Value for Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) or Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables should be populated for all records in Divice In-Use (DU) domain

Error Message: Missing DEVTYPE Parameter for Device
Description: Device Type (DEVTYPE) Parameter must be populated for each Medical Device in the Device Identifiers (DI) domain.

Error Message: Device is not present in DI domain
Description: All Medical Devices (SPDEVID) must be present in Device Identifier (DI) domain.

Error Message: Variable value is longer than defined max length %Variable.@Clause.Length% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level length must not exceed the length as specified define.xml.

Error Message: Variable datatype is not %Variable.@Clause.DataType% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level datatype must match the datatype described in define.xml.

Error Message: Variable value is null when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated when value level attribute Mandatory='Yes' as specified in define.xml file.

Error Message: Multiple NARMS records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'NARMS' Parameter.

Error Message: Variable value not found in user-defined codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated with terms from user-defined value level codelist as specified in define.xml file.

Error Message: Multiple SEXPOP records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'SEXPOP' Parameter.

Error Message: Multiple RANDOM records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'RANDOM' Parameter.

Error Message: Multiple PLANSUB records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'PLANSUB' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for RANDOM
Description: TSVAL for RANDOM record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for PLANSUB
Description: TSVAL for PLANSUB record must be numeric.

Error Message: Multiple LENGTH records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'LENGTH' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for LENGTH
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='LENGTH'.

Error Message: Multiple AGEMIN records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMIN' Parameter.

Error Message: Multiple AGEMAX records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMAX' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for AGEMIN
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMIN'.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for AGEMAX
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMAX'.

Error Message: Multiple ADDON records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'ADDON' Parameter.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a treated subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all treated subjects, those where Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTASSGN', 'NOTTRT', or null.

Error Message: '--STRESN does not equal --STRESC
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be equal Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value, when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Error Message: Missing value for RFICDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) variable value should be populated. It would be NULL only in studies not collecting this info.

Error Message: Missing value for RFXENDTC, when RFXSTDTC is provided
Description: Value for Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value is provided.

Error Message: RFXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: EXENDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: EXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: '--ENDTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: End Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: '--DTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: '--STDTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time (--STDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for IETESTCD within IETEST
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name  (IETESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST).

Error Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Events class domains should be one records per Event per subject. No Events with the same Collected Term (--TERM), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Occurrence (--OCCUR), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT), Directionality (--DIR), Severity (--SEV), Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR), Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Day (VISITDY), and Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) and the same Start Date (--STDTC) are expected.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for IETEST within IETESTCD
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD).

Error Message: Expected variable with missing value for all records
Description: Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When no data has been collected for an Expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the define.xml to state that data was not collected.

Error Message: Missing --PRESP variable, when --OCCUR variable is present
Description: Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable should be included into dataset, when Occurrence (--OCCUR) variable is present. (--PRESP/Events) Used to indicate whether the event describe by --TERM was pre-specified on a CRF.  Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events. (--PRESP/Interventions) Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified on a CRF. Values should be 'Y' or null. (--OCCUR) Used to record whether a pre-specified event occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific event is solicited.

Error Message: MHSTDTC date is after RFSTDTC
Description: The medical history dataset includes the subject's prior history at the start of the trial. Start Date/Time of Medical History Event (MHSTDTC) should be before Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: No Details info for AESMIE Adverse Event in SUPPAE domain
Description: When a description of Other Medically Important Serious Adverse Events category is collected on a CRF, sponsors should place the description in the SUPPAE dataset using the standard supplemental qualifier name code AESOSP.

Error Message: '--DRVFL='Y', when --ORRES value is populated
Description: Derived Flag (--DRVFL) variable may be populated only when Result in Original Units (--ORRES) value is NULL and Result in Std. Format (--STRESC) value is populated (result is derived rather than collected).

Error Message: Non-missing value for --ORRES, when --DRVFL='Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) value should be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for ACTARMCD
Description: A value for Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) with the domain.

Error Message: Missing --STRESC value for Baseline record
Description: A Standard Result value (--STRESC) is expected to be populated for Baseline records (--BLFL='Y').

Error Message: Inconsistent value for QNAM within QLABEL
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL).

Error Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT variables are present
Description: At least one of Age (AGE) or Age Text (AGETXT) variables should be included into Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE)  variable values should be populated with terms 'ONE', 'MANY', when Related Records (RELREC) dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPTNUM within --TPT, --TPTREF, VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPT within --TPTNUM, --TPTREF, VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for  --ELTM within --TPT, --TPTREF and/or VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Elapsed Time (--ELTM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) and/or Visit Number (VISITNUM)

Error Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT values are populated
Description: Value for Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variables should be populated for all subjects. The only exception for SDTM is for Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null.  There are no exceptions for SEND.

Error Message: Comments in SUPPQUAL domain
Description: Comments should be stored in Comments (CO) domain, rather than be put into Supplemental Qualifier (SUPP--) domains.

Error Message: Inappropriate usage of variables in CO domain, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: In the Comments (CO) domain, the following Identifier and Timing variables are Permissible and may be populated as appropriate when comments are not related to other domain records (i.e., RDOMAIN and IDVAR variable values are not populated): COGRPID, COREFID, COSPID, VISIT, VISITNUM, VISITDY, TAETORD, CODY, COTPT, COTPTNUM, COELTM, COTPTREF, CORFTDTC.

Error Message: Neither --STDTC, --DTC nor  --STDY are populated
Description: At least one value of three variables Start Date/Time (--STDTC), Collection Date/Time (--DTC) or Start Study Day (--STDY) should be populated.

Error Message: Inconsistent variable length within split datasets
Description: Split datasets should have matching variable lengths for future merges. Datasets should be resized to the maximum length used prior to splitting.

Error Message: Duplicate records
Description: The structure of Findings class domains should be one record per Finding Result per subject. No Finding Result with the same Test Short Name (--TESTCD) and the same Qualifier variables at the same timepoint for the same Subject (USUBJID) are expected.

Error Message: Value for --BODSYS is in incorrect case
Description: Case for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must follow MedDRA sentence  case and be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --BODSYS not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Missing TE dataset
Description: Trial Elements (TE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing SE dataset
Description: Subject Elements (SE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing DS dataset
Description: Disposition (DS) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing EX dataset
Description: Exposure (EX) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing VS dataset
Description: Vital Signs (VS) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing LB dataset
Description: Lab Test Results (LB) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing AE dataset
Description: Adverse Events (AE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: EPOCH variable is populated, when DSCAT equals 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) variable value should not be populated, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) variable value equals 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'.

Error Message: Missing --STRTPT variable, when --STTPT variable is present
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative Time Point (--STTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --STTPT variable, when --STRTPT variable is present
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --ENRTPT variable, when --ENTPT variable is present
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative Time Point (--ENTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --ENTPT variable, when --ENRTPT variable is present
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --CAT variable, when --SCAT variable is present
Description: Category (--CAT) variable should be included into dataset, when Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --CAT value, when --SCAT value is populated
Description: Value for Category (--CAT) variable should be populated, when value for Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is populated.

Error Message: High risk of truncated value for --TERM variable
Description: SAS v5 export format has a limitation on variables length up to 200 characters. If collected value was more than 200 characters, then SUPPQUAL dataset should be used to store additional 200+ characters. Variable QNAM should have --TERM1, ---TERM2, etc. values for those records. Value splitting should be performed between words or numbers. See SDTM IG #4.1.5.3.2 for details. This risk-assessment check is triggered based on assumption that if original value was truncated, then the actual data value length is exactly 200 characters.

Error Message: Invalid dataset name for split domain
Description: Split datasets must not have name of original domain. E.g., lbhm.xpt is a valid name, when lb.xpt is not a valid dataset name for split domain.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --ENDY variable
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: '--ENDY variable value is imputed
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: '--ENDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --STDY variable
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: '--STDY variable value is imputed
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: '--STDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated, when Start Study Date (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --DY variable
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: '--DY variable value is imputed
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: '--DY variable value is not populated
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated, when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Variable length is too long for actual data
Description: Variable length should be assigned based on actual stored data to minimize file size. Datasets should be re-sized to the maximum length of actual data used prior to splitting.

Error Message: Variable is in wrong order within domain
Description: Order of variables should reflect the order of the variables in the SDTM Model. Variables for the three general observation classes must be ordered with Identifiers first, followed by the Topic, Qualifier, and Timing variables. Within each role, variables must be ordered as shown in SDTM: Tables 2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3, 2.2.4, and 2.2.5.

Error Message: Permissible variable with missing value for all records
Description: Permissible variable should not be present in domain, when the variable has missing value for all records in the dataset.

Error Message: Regulatory Expected variable not found
Description: Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents should be included in the dataset. E.g., EPOCH.

Error Message: Model permissible variable added into standard domain
Description: SDTM model variable may be added into standard domains according its domain general class, if there are no restrictions on their usage specified in IG.

Error Message: Variable not recommended for use
Description: Variables described in IG as not recommended for usage should be not included in the dataset.

Error Message: Variable which can be used only in SEND
Description: Variables designed only for SEND pre-clinical studies must be not included in the SDTM dataset.

Error Message: Variable prohibited for use in SDTM
Description: Variables described in IG as inappropriate for usage must be not included in the dataset.

Error Message: Missing IDVAR value, when RDOMAIN value is provided
Description: Value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable must be populated, when Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable value is provided, with the only exception of 'DM' value for RDOMAIN.

Error Message: Dataset is greater than 5 GB in size
Description: Datasets greater than 5 gigabytes (GB) in size should be split into smaller datasets no larger than 5 GB.

Error Message: USUBJID value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Error Message: IDVARVAL value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Variable Value (IDVARVAL) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Error Message: Missing RDOMAIN value, when IDVAR is populated
Description: Value of Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable must be populated, when value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable is populated.

Error Message: Dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Datasets included in study data must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Error Message: AESER is not 'Y', when AESOD equals 'Y'
Description: Serious Event (AESER) variable value is expected to be 'Y', when Occurred with Overdose (AESOD) variable value equals 'Y'.

Error Message: Missing MB dataset, when MS dataset is present
Description: Microbiology Specimen (MB) dataset should be included, when a Microbiology Susceptibility Test (MS) dataset is present.

Error Message: Duplicate VISITNUM
Description: The value of Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable should be unique for each record within a subject.

Error Message: Unexpected value for ARMCD variable
Description: Records for subjects who failed a screening or were not assigned to study treatment (ARMCD is 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN') should not be included in the Trial Arms (TA) or Trial Visits (TV) datasets.

Error Message: Non-unique value for TAETORD within ARMCD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) must have a unique value for a given value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) within the domain.

Error Message: Unexpected value for IDVAR/IDVARVAL
Description: Both Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) should not be populated, when relating information to the Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Invalid value for QLABEL
Description: Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) value may have up to 40 characters.

Error Message: Both --DOSE and --DOSTXT values are populated
Description: Only one of Dose (--DOSE) or Dose Description (--DOSTXT) variables must be populated on the same record.

Error Message: Inconsistent values for IEORRES/IECAT
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'N', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'INCLUSION'.

Error Message: Inconsistent values for IEORRES/IECAT
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'Y', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'EXCLUSION'.

Error Message: No --BLFL variable in custom Findings domain
Description: Baseline Flag (--BLFL) should be present in all custom Findings domains.

Error Message: Time point for non-occurred event or intervention is provided
Description: Value of Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated, when an event or intervention is marked as not occurred (--OCCUR='N').

Error Message: Values for --CAT and --SCAT are identical
Description: Values of Category (--CAT) and Subcategory (--SCAT) variables should not be identical.

Error Message: '--SCAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Subcategory (--SCAT) should not be  identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: '--CAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Category (--CAT) should not be identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: Non-unique value for TSSEQ variable within TSPARMCD
Description: Sequence Number (TSSEQ) must have a  unique value for a given value of Trial Summary Parameter Short Name (TSPARMCD) within the domain.

Error Message: Missing value for --TOX, when --TOXGR is populated
Description: A value for a Toxicity (--TOX) variable should be provided, when a Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable value is populated and greater than 0.

Error Message: Missing value for --TOXGR, when --TOX is populated
Description: Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) should be provided, when Toxicity (--TOX) is populated.

Error Message: No records for 'SCRNFAIL' subject are found in IE domain
Description: All subjects with Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) equals 'SCRNFAIL' should have records in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) domain.

Error Message: Value for --ENRF is populated, when RFENDTC is NULL
Description: End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Error Message: Value for --STRF is populated, when RFSTDTC is NULL
Description: Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: Non-unique value for ELEMENT within ETCD
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) must have a unique value for a given value of Element Code (ETCD) within the domain.

Error Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE) must be NULL, when Identifying Variable (IDVAR) is populated with a --SEQ value.

Error Message: VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match TV domain data
Description: Combination of Visit Name (VISIT) and Visit Number (VISITNUM) in subject-level domains should match that in the TV domain with the exception of Unscheduled and Unplanned visits.

Error Message: Invalid value for QNAM variable
Description: The value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Error Message: Missing DM dataset
Description: Demographics (DM) dataset must be included in every submission.

Error Message: VISITDY is populated for unplanned visit
Description: Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) should equal NULL for unplanned visits, where Description of Unplanned Visit (SVUPDES) is populated.

Error Message: VISITNUM/VISIT/VISITDY values do not match TV domain data
Description: The combination of Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Name (VISIT), and Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Error Message: VISITNUM value does not match TV domain data
Description: Visit Number (VISITNUM) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Error Message: Invalid IETESTCD/IETEST/IECAT
Description: The combination of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD), Criterion (IETEST), and Category (IECAT) values should match entries in the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) dataset.

Error Message: Invalid EPOCH
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Error Message: Invalid TAETORD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Error Message: TAETORD is populated, ETCD = 'UNPLAN'
Description: Planned Order of Elements within Arm (TAETORD) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid ETCD/ELEMENT
Description: The combination of Element Code (ETCD) and Description of Element (ELEMENT) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Duration, Elapsed Time, and Interval variables (--DUR, --ELTM, --EVLINT, --STINT, --ENINT, TDSTOFF, TDTGTPAI, TDMINPAI, TDMAXPAI) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Error Message: ELEMENT value is populated, when ETCD= 'UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: Invalid value for ETCD
Description: The value of Element Code (ETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: CODTC is populated, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: The value of Date/Time of Comment (CODTC) should be NULL, when comments are related to a specific parent record or group of parent records in a domain (RDOMAIN, IDVAR and IDVARVAL are populated).

Error Message: Invalid STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values must match the STUDYID in Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Invalid value for ARMCD
Description: The value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Error Message: Missing value for AGE, when AGEU is provided
Description: Age (AGE) should be provided, when Age Units (AGEU) are populated.

Error Message: Duplicate SUBJID
Description: The value of Subject Identifier for the Study (SUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject within the study.

Error Message: Invalid usage of SUPPQUAL for non-general-observation-class Domain
Description: Supplemental Qualifiers special purpose dataset (SUPP--) can only be used to capture non-standard variables and their association to parent records in general-observation-class datasets (Events, Findings, Interventions) and Demographics. Another exception is Subject Visits domain in SDTM-IG prior v3.4

Error Message: Missing value for AGEU, when AGE is provided
Description: Age Units (AGEU) should be provided, when Age (AGE) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for SEUPDES, when ETCD='UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) should be populated, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: AEOUT is not 'FATAL', when AESDTH='Y'
Description: Outcome of Adverse Event should equal 'FATAL', when Results in Death (AESDTH) is 'Y'.

Error Message: AESDTH is not 'Y', when AEOUT='FATAL'
Description: Results in Death (AESDTH) should equal 'Y', when Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT)  is 'FATAL'.

Error Message: Missing values for TEENRL and TEDUR
Description: At least one of Rule for End of Element (TEENRL) or Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be populated.

Error Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Error Message: SUPPQUAL duplicate records
Description: All SUPPQUAL Domains records are associated with a single parent record and must have a unique combination of Study Identifier (STUDYID), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR), Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) and Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) variable value. For all SUPPQUAL domain record all The QNAM variable should be unique for each parent record.

Error Message: Mismatch between IEORRES and IESTRESC values
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) and I/E Criterion Result in Std Format (IESTRESC) should have the same value.

Error Message: Duplicate USUBJID in DM within STUDYID
Description: The value of Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject across all trials in the submission. In the Demographics (DM) domain, there should only be one record per subject.

Error Message: AE start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Adverse Event (AESTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: EX record is present, when subject is not assigned to an arm
Description: Subjects that are not assigned to an Arm (ARMCD='NOTASSGN') or are screen failures (ARMCD='SCRNFAIL'), or ARM=null, should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Error Message: Invalid referenced record
Description: Reference record defined by Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) must exist in the target Domain.

Error Message: Invalid IDVAR
Description: Identifying Variable (IDVAR) must have a valid value of variables from a referenced Domain.

Error Message: Invalid RDOMAIN
Description: Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) must have a valid value of Domains included in the study data.

Error Message: Invalid ARM/ARMCD
Description: The combination of Description of Planned Arm (ARM) and Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values must match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Error Message: No Exposure record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) participating in a study that includes investigational product should have at least one record in the Exposure (EX) domain, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL'), were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN'), or did not receive study treatment (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

Error Message: No Disposition record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) should have at least one record in the Disposition (DS) domain. The only possible exceptions for SDTMIG v3.2 (and earlier) are Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned Treatment (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null.  There are no exceptions for SEND.

Error Message: Invalid IETESTCD
Description: A value for Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be present the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) domain.

Error Message: Invalid ETCD
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid ARMCD
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Error Message: USUBJID/VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match SV domain data
Description: All Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) + Visit Name (VISIT) + Visit Number (VISITNUM) combination values in data should be present in the Subject Visits (SV) domain. There is an exception for records, where Status (--STAT) variable value is populated. E.g., --STAT = 'NOT DONE'. Another exception is for records, where Occurrence (ECOCCUR) is 'N' in EC domain.

Error Message: Subject is not present in DM domain
Description: All Subjects (USUBJID) must be present in Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Error Message: Incompatible data source
Description: Domain table must have a valid format (e.g., SAS transport (XPORT) v.5 or text-delimited).

Error Message: Domain referenced in define.xml but dataset is missing
Description: Domains referenced in data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the submission.

Error Message: Variable in dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Variables included in the dataset must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable DataType in define.xml must match variable Type in dataset. Define-XML data types of 'integer' and 'float' match dataset type of 'Num', all other match 'Char'.

Error Message: Variable appears in dataset, but is not in SDTM model
Description: Only variables listed in SDTM model should appear in a dataset. New sponsor defined variables must not be added, and existing variables must not be renamed or modified.

Error Message: SDTM Expected variable not found
Description: Variables described in SDTM IG as Expected should be included in the dataset.

Error Message: SDTM Required variable not found
Description: Variables described in SDTM IG as Required must be included in the dataset.

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable Data Types in the dataset should match the variable data types described in SDTM.

Error Message: Variable in define.xml is not present in the dataset
Description: Variables listed in the data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the dataset.

Error Message: ARM is not 'Not Assigned', when ARMCD equals 'NOTASSGN', or vice versa
Description: Description of Arm (ARM) must equal 'Not Assigned', when Arm Code (ARMCD) is 'NOTASSGN', and vice versa.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for VISITNUM within VISIT
Description: All values of Visit Number (VISITNUM) should be the same for a given value of Visit Name (VISIT).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for VISIT within VISITNUM
Description: All values of Visit Name (VISIT) should be the same for a given value of Visit Number (VISITNUM).

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --STAT or --DRVFL is not populated
Description: Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE' or Derived Flag (--DRVFL) should have a value of 'Y', when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is NULL.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --RESCAT is populated
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should be provided, when Result Category (--RESCAT) is specified.

Error Message: Missing value for --VAMTU, when --VAMT is populated
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) should not be NULL,  when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TRTV, when --VAMT is not NULL
Description: Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) should be provided, when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is specified.

Error Message: '--STAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', when --PRESP='Y' and --OCCUR is NULL
Description: When no response is provided for Occurrence (--OCCUR) for a pre-specified Intervention or Event (--PRESP = 'Y'), then Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE'.

Error Message: Value for --OCCUR is populated for unsolicited Intervention or Event
Description: Occurrence (--OCCUR) may only be populated, when a given Intervention or Event has been pre-specified (--PRESP = 'Y').

Error Message: Value of Study Day variable equals 0
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not equal 0.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) must be populated, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --DOSU, when --DOSE, --DOSTXT or --DOSTOT is provided
Description: Dose Units (--DOSU) must be populated, when Dose per Administration (--DOSE), Dose Description (--DOSTXT) or Total Daily Dose (--DOSTOT) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPTREF, when --ELTM is provided
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) should not be NULL, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPTNUM, when --TPT is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPT, when --TPTNUM is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) is populated.

Error Message: Missing values for --STDTC, --STRF and --STRTPT, when --ENDTC, --ENRF or --ENRTPT is provided
Description: Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC), Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) should not be NULL, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC), End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) or End Relative to Reference Time Period (--ENRTPT) is not NULL.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STRESU is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should not be NULL, when Standard Units (--STRESU) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESU, when --STRESC is provided
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) should not be NULL, when Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) is provided as a numeric result.

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --ORRESU is provided
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should not be NULL, when Original Units (--ORRESU) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRESU, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Original Units (--ORRESU) should not be NULL, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided is a numeric result.

Error Message: Missing Start Time-Point value
Description: One Start Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or intervention occurred. (E.g., Start Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--STDTC), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '').

Error Message: Missing value for --STAT, when --REASND is provided
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE', when Reason Not Done (--REASND) is populated.

Error Message: Missing End Time-Point value
Description: One End Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or an intervention occurred. (E.g., End Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--ENDTC), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '') or Duration (--DUR) != '').

Error Message: Invalid value for --PARMCD variable
Description: The value of Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid value for --PARM variable
Description: The value of Parameter (--PARM) variable should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid value for --TESTCD variable
Description: The value of a Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) variable should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Error Message: Invalid value for --TEST variable
Description: The value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --DRVFL='Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Error Message: ARM is not 'Screen Failure', when ARMCD equals 'SCRNFAIL', or vice versa
Description: Description of Arm (ARM) must equal 'Screen Failure',  when Arm Code (ARMCD) is 'SCRNFAIL', and vice versa.

Error Message: No qualifiers set to 'Y', when AE is Serious
Description: When Serious Event (AESER) variable value is 'Y', then at least one of seriousness criteria variables is expected to have value 'Y' (Involves Cancer (AESCAN), Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect (AESCONG), Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity (AESDISAB), Results in Death (AESDTH), Requires or Prolongs Hospitalization (AESHOSP), Is Life Threatening (AESLIFE), or Other Medically Important Serious Event (AESMIE)).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD is in incorrect case
Description: Case for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be sentence case using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: No baseline flag record in Domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have at least one baseline observation (--BLFL = 'Y') in EG, LB, MB, MS, PC and VS domains, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN') or were not treated (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) or Pool Identifier (POOLID) variables value when they are present in the domain. Exclusions are DO, DT, DU and DX domains.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for DOMAIN
Description: Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN) variable should be consistent with the name of the dataset.

Error Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Dates/Time variables (*DTC) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Error Message: NULL value in variable marked as Required
Description: Required variables (where Core attribute is 'Req') cannot be NULL for any records.

Error Message: No records in data source
Description: Domain table should have at least one record.

Error Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT when value-level condition occurs
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value within the same value level condition.

Error Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value.

Error Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: DSCAT equals PROTOCOL MILESTONE but DSTERM is not equal to DSDECOD
Description: When DSCAT equals PROTOCOL MILESTONE, then DSTERM should be equal to DSDECOD

Error Message: Invalid whodrug code hierarcy
Description: MEDDRA CODE TERM PAIRS are wrong for SOCCD

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist.
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: PESTRESC does not equal PEORRES OR a dictionary coded preferred term
Description: Trigger error when PESTRESC ^= null but PESTRESC does not equal PEORRES OR a dictionary coded preferred term

Error Message: RSUBJID must be missing when RDEVID is populated
Description: Verify that RSUBJID is empty when RDEVID is populated

Error Message: RDEVID must be empty when RSUBJID is populated and RSUBJID must be empty when RDEVID is populated
Description: Related Device Identifier (RDEVID) and Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) should not both be populated for the same record.

Error Message: When RSUBJID is populated, RUSBJID cannot equal POOLID
Description: Verify when RSUBJID is populated it does not equal POOLID

Error Message: Test is for culture characteristics, but MBTEST is not the name of the  organism or group of organisms.
Description: If the test is for culture characteristics, verify that MBTEST equals the name of the  organism/antigen being characterized.

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but
Description: Verify MBTESTCD is "MCORGIDN" if the test is for a non-targeted identification of organisms.

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but MBTSTDTL is not "DETECTION"
Description: Verify MBTSTDTL is "DETECTION" if the tests targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen.

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but MBTEST is not the name of the  organism/antigen.
Description: Verify MBTEST equals the name of the organism/antigen targeted by the identification assay.

Error Message: Parameter is non-normalized and terminology of PPSTRESU is not for a non-normalized parameter
Description: Trigger error when parameter is non-normalized and terminology of PPSTRESU is not for a non-normalized parameter

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by weight
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by weight

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by dose amount
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by dose amount

Error Message: '--STREFN is not in the same units as --STRESN
Description: Trigger error when --STREFN is not in the same units as --STRESN

Error Message: '--ORREF is not in the same units as --ORRES
Description: Trigger error when --ORREF is not in the same units as --ORRES

Error Message: MIDS is not suffixed with a sequence number in consistent chronological order
Description: Trigger error when MIDSTYPE=TM.MIDSTYPE and TM.TMRPT=Y and MIDS is not suffixed with a sequence number in consistent chronological order

Error Message: RACE does not equal "MULTIPLE" when multiple races collected and primary race not specified
Description: Trigger error when RACE does not equal "MULTIPLE" when multiple races collected and primary race not specified

Error Message: RACE is not equal to "UNKNOWN" when subject did not specify race
Description: Trigger error when subject does not specify race and RACE is not equal to "UNKNOWN"
Trigger error when Sponsor collects Other, specify and chooses to map the value to SUPPDM, and NOT - RACE = 'OTHER' or RACE = 'MULTIPLE'

Error Message: ACTARMCD is populated for a subject who was not assigned to treatment
Description: Trigger error when ACTARMCD is populated for a subject who was not assigned to treatment

Error Message: ARMCD is populated for a subject who was not assigned to treatment
Description: Trigger error when ARMCD is populated for a subject who was not assigned to treatment

Error Message: '--LLOQ is not expressed using the units in --STRESU
Description: Trigger error when --LLOQ is not expressed using the units in --STRESU

Error Message: '--HLGT is not on the path to MedDRA primary system organ class
Description: Trigger error when --HLGT is not on the path to MedDRA primary system organ class

Error Message: '--HLT is not on the path to MedDRA primary system organ class
Description: Trigger error when --HLT is not on the path to MedDRA primary system organ class

Error Message: TDANCVAR is not valid
Description: Trigger error when TDANCVAR is not a date variable name in ADSL

Error Message: '--LLT is not a valid MedDRA lowest level TERM
Description: Trigger error when --LLT  is not a valid MedDRA lowest level TERM

Error Message: '--LLTCD  is not a valid MedDRA lowest level code
Description: Trigger error when --LLTCD  is not a valid MedDRA lowest level code

Error Message: '--DECOD  is not a valid MedDRA preferred TERM
Description: Trigger error when --DECOD  is not a valid MedDRA preferred TERM

Error Message: '--PTCD  is not a valid MedDRA preferred term code
Description: Trigger error when --PTCD  is not a valid MedDRA preferred term code

Error Message: '--HLT  is not a valid MedDRA high level TERM
Description: Trigger error when --HLT  is not a valid MedDRA high level TERM

Error Message: '--HLTCD  is not a valid MedDRA high level TERM code
Description: Trigger error when --HLTCD  is not a valid MedDRA high level TERM code

Error Message: '--HLGT  is not a valid MedDRA high level group TERM
Description: Trigger error when --HLGT  is not a valid MedDRA high level group TERM

Error Message: '--HLGTCD  is not a valid MedDRA high level group TERM code
Description: Trigger error when --HLGTCD  is not a valid MedDRA high level group TERM code

Error Message: '--BODSYS  is not a valid MedDRA system organ class
Description: Trigger error when --BODSYS  is not a valid MedDRA system organ class

Error Message: '--LOINC is not a valid code in the version of the LOINC dictionary specified in define.xml
Description: Trigger error when --LOINC is not a valid code in the version of the LOINC dictionary specified in define.xml

Error Message: Variable within SUPPQUAL is in Model List of Allowed Variables for Observation Class
Description: Trigger error when a variable in Model List of Allowed Variables for Observation Class is in SUPPQUAL

Error Message: TEENRL refers to a specific ARM
Description: TEENRL should not reference a specific ARM.  This rule has only been partially executed to identify explicit references to ARM.

Error Message: ELEMENT refers to a specific EPOCH when ELEMENT is associated with more than 1 EPOCH
Description: When ELEMENT is associated with more than 1 EPOCH, ELEMENT should not refer to a specific EPOCH.

Error Message: ELEMENT value refers to a specific ARM when ELEMENT is associated with more than 1 arm
Description: When ELEMENT is associated with more than 1 arm, the ELEMENT value must not refer to a specific ARM

Error Message: Relationship represented in RELREC is not a collected relationship
Description: Trigger error when relationship represented in RELREC is not a collected relationship

Error Message: MIDS variable is missing when MIDSDTC variable is present in a dataset.
Description: Raise an error when variable MIDSDTC is present and MIDS variable is missing.

Error Message: TM dataset is missing when MIDS variable is present in one of the dataset.
Description: Raise an error when variable MIDS is present in any of the dataset and TM dataset is missing.

Error Message: VISIT is not described in the protocol
Description: Trigger error when a visit is not described in the protocol
Trigger error when ARM is populated and the timing and number of Visits for a trial does not depend on which ARM a subject is in

Error Message: ARMCD is populated and the timing and number of Visits for a trial does not depend on which ARM a subject is in
Description: Trigger error when ARMCD is populated and the timing and number of Visits for a trial does not depend on which ARM a subject is in

Error Message: TIVERS is not present in the data when there is more than one version of the IE criteria
Description: Trigger error when TIVERS is not present in the data and there is more than one version of the IE criteria

Error Message: TABRANCH is null when trial design branches
Description: Trigger error when trial design branches and TABRANCH is null

Error Message: At least one EPOCH is associated with more than one conceptual trial period
Description: Trigger error when at least one EPOCH is associated with more than one conceptual trial period

Error Message: TATRANS is populated when the element does not end with a decision that could lead to a shortened path within the Arm
Description: Trigger error when element does not end with a decision that could lead to a shortened path within the Arm and TATRANS is not null

Error Message: '--DTC is present in dataset and is not populated with the date/time of recording/data acquisition
Description: Trigger error when --DTC is present and not populated with the date/time of recording/data acquisition

Error Message: '--DTC is date/time of recording/acquisition, not date/time of specimen collection or observation
Description: Trigger error when --DTC is date/time of recording/acquisition, not date/time of specimen collection or observation

Error Message: The MB dataset is not present when the MS dataset is present.
Description: Trigger error if MS dataset is present and MB dataset is not present.

Error Message: LBSTNRC is not expressed using the units in LBSTRESU when LBSTRESU is populated.
